+# Exploration 001 Summary
+
+## Goal
+
+Decide whether this mission has one intrinsic exact-helical phase/coherence
+observable that survives the Phase 0 definition gate, or whether every honest
+candidate collapses into packet bookkeeping, representative-choice instability,
+or amplitude-only language.
+
+## What I tried
+
+- Reused the exact helical triad law and singleton-support audit from the
+  earlier exact Tao-circuit mission.
+- Rejected the inherited packet-sign families as non-canonical.
+- Compared two intrinsic candidate shapes on an interface-based exact triad
+  population:
+  - raw phase concentration,
+  - signed-transfer versus absolute-transfer coherence defect.
+- Reused the hidden-precursor event only as a fidelity anchor, then stripped the
+  spatial cutoff to define a cleaner spectral delayed-transfer companion event.
+
+## Outcome
+
+Succeeded, narrowly.
+
+## Key Takeaway
+
+The preferred Phase 0 object is not a Tao-role or packet observable. It is the
+exact **transfer-coherence ratio**
+
+```text
+C_ℓ(t) = (∑ T_{τ,ℓ}(t)) / (∑ |T_{τ,ℓ}(t)|)
+```
+
+on the full sign-closed helical triad population contributing to one smooth
+scale-interface transfer ledger, with defect `D_ℓ = 1 - C_ℓ`.
+
+## Leads Worth Pursuing
+
+- Run the smallest honest exact-support audit for the pair
+  `(C_ℓ, E_ℓ^transfer)`.
+- Decide whether `C_ℓ` is genuinely informative there or only a dressed-up
+  cancellation ratio.
+
+## Unexpected Findings
+
+- The existing localized physical-space event `E_flux` is close in spirit but
+  not the clean preferred companion event for the phase observable, because the
+  spatial cutoff obscures the exact triad ledger.
+- The clean pair is obtained by keeping the same smooth scale interface and
+  dropping the localization.
+
+## Computations Worth Doing Later
+
+- Minimal-support or smallest-cluster computations that test whether delayed
+  transfer can stay live while `C_ℓ` remains small.
